SManager"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/ManagerCreation","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/managercreation","type":"topic","kind":"project","title":"Creating and managing TWSManager","estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/RemoteSnippet":{"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/remotesnippet","title":"Display your first remote snippet","kind":"project","role":"project","estimatedTime":"3min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to set up a manager to handle the logic and functionality of your snippets, as well as how to seamlessly integrate them into your SwiftUI views."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents/Display-your-first-snippet":{"url":"\/tutorials\/tutorial-table-of-contents\/display-your-first-snippet","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[],"title":"Display your first snippet","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents\/Display-your-first-snippet","type":"topic"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/MixAndMatch":{"url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/mixandmatch","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"5min","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/MixAndMatch","title":"Combine remote and local snippets","abstract":[{"text":"Once you start mixing remote and local snippets, there are a few important considerations to keep in mind. Since the manager is injected into the environment, it can be accessed from anywhere in the app. However, this setup assumes that snippets are handled remotely. To successfully work with both remote and local snippets, you’ll need to follow specific rules and best practices.","type":"text"}],"role":"project","kind":"project"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/Notifications":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/Notifications","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/notifications","role":"project","title":"Integrating TWSNotifications with your notifications","estimatedTime":"3min","abst